{{italic title}}
The '''''Enciclopedia Dantesca''''', published 1970–1975 by the [[Istituto dell'Enciclopedia Italiana]], in six volumes, under the general editorship of [[Umberto Bosco]], is considered the reference book in [[Italian language]] about the life and works of [[Dante Alighieri|Dante]],<ref name="Danteworlds, 3" /> described as a "monumental" work<ref name="Danteworlds, 3">{{cite book|last=Raffa|first=Guy P.|title=Danteworlds: A Reader's Guide to the Inferno|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=nCYsixmgeYYC&pg=PA3|accessdate=11 April 2012|year=2007|publisher=[[University of Chicago Press]]|isbn=978-0-226-70268-1|page=3}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author=Dante Alighieri|editor=[[Stanley Lombardo]]|title=Inferno|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=SXX9pMFCR8IC&pg=PR43|accessdate=11 April 2012|year=2009|publisher=[[Hackett Publishing Company|Hackett]]|isbn=978-0-87220-917-6|page=43}}</ref>

