[[File:Entrance - MBA - DSC06932.JPG|thumb|Entrance to the [[Monterey Aquarium]], located in the former Hovden Cannery building]] [[File:DSC26543, Monterey Bay Aquarium, California, USA (8410270912).jpg|thumb|Hovden Cannery display in the Monterey Aquarium]] The '''Hovden Cannery''' in [[Cannery Row]], [[Monterey, California]] was among the oldest, largest [[canneries]] of the [[Pacific Sardine Fishery]]. In the first half of the 20th century, it marked one of the most lucrative national [[fisheries]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.loc.gov/pictures/item/CA1292/ |title=Hovden Cannery, 886 Cannery Row, Monterey, Monterey County, CA |work=Library of Congress |publisher=Library of Congress |accessdate=2016-01-30 }}{{PD-notice}}</ref> It was a source for literary inspiration in the works of [[John Steinbeck]].<ref>{{cite web|author1=Phyllis J. Hanniver|title=Even Steinbeck Might Have Trouble Writing About Cannery Row Today|url=http://articles.latimes.com/1990-02-18/travel/tr-1449_1_cannery-row|publisher=LA Times|accessdate=18 February 2016|date=February 18, 1990}}</ref>
Hovden Cannery was founded in 1916 by Knute Hovden, a leading innovator in canning technology, and closed in 1973 after the collapse of the area fish population.<ref>{{cite web|title=Cannery Row offers hints of its history|url=http://www.sfgate.com/travel/article/Cannery-Row-offers-hints-of-its-history-4812835.php|publisher=SF Gate|accessdate=18 February 2016|date=September 16, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author1=Donald Fitzgerald|title=The history and significance of the Hovden Cannery, Cannery Row, Monterey, California, 1914-1973|url=https://searchworks.stanford.edu/view/4729562|accessdate=18 February 2016|location=Stanford University Library|date=1979}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Rise of the canneries|url=http://www.montereyherald.com/20101226/rise-of-the-canneries|publisher=Monterey Herald|accessdate=18 February 2016|date=December 26, 2010}}</ref>
The former cannery building is now the site of the [[Monterey Bay Aquarium]], which opened in 1984.<ref>{{cite web|title=Our History|url=http://www.montereybayaquarium.org/about/our-history|publisher=Monterey Aquarium|accessdate=18 February 2016}}</ref>
