{{Infobox book <!-- |italic title = (see above) --> | name = The Outdoor Survival Handbook | image = FrontCoverofTheOutdoorSurvivalHandbook.jpg | caption = | alt = | author = Raymond Mears | title_orig = The Complete Outdoor Handbook | orig_lang_code = | title_working = | translator = | illustrator = Paul Bryant | cover_artist = Heather Kim | country = | language = English | series = | subject = | genre = Survival | published = 1992 | media_type = Print (paperback) | pages = 240 | awards = | isbn = 0-312-09359-4 | oclc = | dewey = | congress = | preceded_by = | followed_by = | wikisource = }} '''''The Outdoor Survival Handbook''''' is a 1992 [[Survivalism|survival]] book by [[Ray Mears]]. First published as ''The Complete Outdoor Handbook''; The book is divided into four sections, one for each [[season]] with chapters on clothing, survival skills and [[tool]]s for each.<ref>[https://www.amazon.com/Outdoor-Survival-Handbook-Resources-Navigation/dp/0312093594 "Amazon.com, ''The Outdoor Survival Handbook: A Guide To The Resources...''] "Amazon.com", Accessed 2011-7-19.</ref> Includes illustrations by Paul Bryant. ==References== {{reflist}}
